1
00:00:00,125 --> 00:00:01,959
During ISIS’s presence

2
00:00:02,918 --> 00:00:05,125
Unfortunately, this holy church

3
00:00:05,834 --> 00:00:09,751
They would turn it into a prison or commit crimes in it

4
00:00:09,876 --> 00:00:13,709
Isn’t this God’s house, where Christians speak the name of God?

5
00:00:13,792 --> 00:00:14,918
And remember their religion there

6
00:00:15,209 --> 00:00:18,459
Why do you do this in the homes of people you have wronged?

7
00:00:19,209 --> 00:00:22,450
This church became a prison, they turned it into a prison

8
00:00:22,834 --> 00:00:23,876
Unfortunately, a prison

9
00:00:24,125 --> 00:00:26,626
When the Christians were here, it was a place of freedom

10
00:00:27,042 --> 00:00:29,959
They were free, they welcomed you warmly

11
00:00:30,334 --> 00:00:33,083
You would sit in their religious rituals

12
00:00:33,375 --> 00:00:37,626
There is a vast difference between those who welcomed you and those who turned the place into a prison

13
00:00:37,876 --> 00:00:38,959
And a place of misery for people

14
00:00:39,375 --> 00:00:41,167
Where people are flogged and killed

15
00:00:41,542 --> 00:00:44,250
I do not know how to describe it to you, it is hard

16
00:00:45,584 --> 00:00:47,876
The Christian community is the opposite of them

17
00:00:47,918 --> 00:00:48,918
And look at how they are

18
00:00:48,959 --> 00:00:52,375
How the Christians used to welcome you, they would treat you like a guest of honor

19
00:00:53,083 --> 00:00:57,667
They give you chocolate, you sit, and they bring you cold water

20
00:00:57,959 --> 00:00:59,083
The priest welcomes you

21
00:00:59,375 --> 00:01:01,584
Those others were committing crimes

22
00:01:01,626 --> 00:01:03,083
You see the ugliest scenes

23
00:01:03,375 --> 00:01:06,125
The prisoner, the one whose eyes are blindfolded, whose hands are shackled

24
00:01:06,167 --> 00:01:07,167
In this church

25
00:01:07,209 --> 00:01:10,667
How that welcomed people, and how this one receives people

26
00:01:10,959 --> 00:01:12,334
Look at the vast difference

27
00:01:13,959 --> 00:01:14,959
Interviewer: Ahmad

28
00:01:16,751 --> 00:01:18,918
After ISIS left Mosul

29
00:01:19,584 --> 00:01:21,709
After ISIS left Mosul

30
00:01:22,125 --> 00:01:24,834
When was the last time you visited this place?

31
00:01:24,959 --> 00:01:27,584
Meaning after ISIS left the city

32
00:01:28,834 --> 00:01:32,542
Witness: Four months after the liberation

33
00:01:33,042 --> 00:01:35,959
We came to visit this area, to our homes

34
00:01:37,459 --> 00:01:40,792
As soon as I came from this street by Shaareen Market

35
00:01:41,250 --> 00:01:42,709
There was a checkpoint there

36
00:01:42,959 --> 00:01:44,042
Here there was nothing

37
00:01:44,083 --> 00:01:46,626
So I would not go that way

38
00:01:47,209 --> 00:01:50,083
I came in here and went out from this place

39
00:01:50,459 --> 00:01:52,918
This place was open before they built the churches

40
00:01:53,167 --> 00:01:55,792
I went in through the churches, and I was moved by them

41
00:01:56,250 --> 00:01:58,375
Before I went to my house, I had not gone home yet

42
00:01:58,709 --> 00:02:00,709
I swear, I came straight here

43
00:02:00,751 --> 00:02:02,292
Interviewer: I want you to describe how you felt

44
00:02:02,292 --> 00:02:05,292
My feelings, God is my witness, I cried

45
00:02:06,334 --> 00:02:10,542
I cried and first remembered their conduct

46
00:02:10,584 --> 00:02:13,459
And second, I saw the churches destroyed

47
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:16,542
And I used to take part in their rituals

48
00:02:16,959 --> 00:02:19,918
They do not deserve this to happen to them, they do not deserve it

49
00:02:20,500 --> 00:02:22,459
They are kind, peaceful, and trustworthy people

50
00:02:22,751 --> 00:02:25,083
They respected you and treated you like a guest of honor

51
00:02:25,626 --> 00:02:28,292
And then you, ISIS member, come and treat them like this, and destroy the churches

52
00:02:28,334 --> 00:02:30,500
This is not right, you have wronged them severely

53
00:02:30,876 --> 00:02:33,500
It cannot be described, I swear to you

54
00:02:33,667 --> 00:02:35,959
I was affected by it, I walked while crying

55
00:02:36,042 --> 00:02:37,459
Even though no one could see me

56
00:02:37,709 --> 00:02:41,000
When no one sees a person, he does not feel ashamed, so he cries

57
00:02:41,042 --> 00:02:43,542
So I climbed over the rubble and stones

58
00:02:43,918 --> 00:02:45,167
And after that I did not go to my house

59
00:02:45,292 --> 00:02:47,792
I came to see my house, but I came from here

60
00:02:47,834 --> 00:02:50,751
I entered by the Old Bridge as a shortcut through the churches

61
00:02:51,250 --> 00:02:52,584
And I came to Shaareen Market

62
00:02:52,792 --> 00:02:55,417
I went in through the churches, and I saw them destroyed

63
00:02:56,209 --> 00:03:02,500
My heart burned, and I cried intensely, and I was affected by it

64
00:03:03,417 --> 00:03:06,125
I felt deep anguish, I was deeply affected

65
00:03:08,292 --> 00:03:09,709
Interviewer: Before we conclude

66
00:03:10,959 --> 00:03:14,292
I want you to tell me, do you think the congregation of this church

67
00:03:14,959 --> 00:03:18,584
Or the people who were responsible for it

68
00:03:19,125 --> 00:03:22,667
Will they be able to move beyond this painful period

69
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:26,626
In the building’s history and create new memories?

70
00:03:27,375 --> 00:03:30,292
Witness: Yes, they can, because they have patience

71
00:03:30,876 --> 00:03:32,000
They have suffered

72
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:35,751
And their anguish grew intense

73
00:03:36,375 --> 00:03:38,334
They were subjected to severe injustice

74
00:03:38,751 --> 00:03:42,292
So with their morale and their patience

75
00:03:42,876 --> 00:03:45,042
And with their beautiful faith

76
00:03:45,417 --> 00:03:49,292
It will return gradually, it will not return quickly

77
00:03:49,751 --> 00:03:53,250
They are sincere—they will rebuild it with their resolve and their shoulders

78
00:03:53,626 --> 00:03:55,459
With their words and their way

79
00:03:55,834 --> 00:03:57,209
With their sincerity and their honesty

80
00:03:57,834 --> 00:03:59,584
Remember my words, these churches will return

81
00:03:59,626 --> 00:04:00,959
And they will do an even better job, God willing

82
00:04:01,167 --> 00:04:04,792
Just as Shaareen Market came back, and Sarjkhana came back

83
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:06,209
And Bab al-Saray came back

84
00:04:06,584 --> 00:04:09,584
They will restore it with God’s help, just as those areas returned

85
00:04:10,083 --> 00:04:11,834
Because this is their ritual and their faith

86
00:04:12,083 --> 00:04:14,125
Faith should be held above all

87
00:04:14,375 --> 00:04:16,108
A person must struggle for it
